<HL>
   Who's News:
   John Wiley's Ellis
   Is Appointed Chief
</HL>
<DATE>
05/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8
</SO>
<CO>
   WILLA WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- John Wiley &amp; Sons Inc., an independent book
publishing company, said it named Charles R. Ellis president
and chief executive officer, succeeding Ruth R. McMullin, who
resigned, effective next Thursday.
   Mr. Ellis, 54 years old, is an executive vice president of
Wiley and president of its Wiley Publishing Group unit. The
company specializes in scientific, technical and business
titles.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said Mrs. McMullin, 47, is leaving voluntarily
to pursue personal interests. Before being named chief
executive last year, she was the company's chief operating
officer for two years.
</TEXT>
